name: 5-iodoindole
Reason: 5-iodoindole has a melting point that we can compare to by analyzing its structural components: (1) The indole ring itself contributes to the melting point due to its rigidity and pi-system, estimated at around +20 °C; (2) The iodine atom introduces a significant dipole, increasing intermolecular forces and melting point by approximately +50 °C.
